'''Baldet Crater''' is an [[impact crater]] in the [[Syrtis Major quadrangle]] of [[Mars]], located at 23.0°N latitude and 294.6°W longitude. It is 180.0 &nbsp;km in diameter and was named after [[Fernand Baldet]], and the name was approved in 1973 by the International Astronomical Union (IAU) Working Group for Planetary System Nomenclature (WGPSN).<ref>{{cite web|title=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature {{!}} Baldet|url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/575|website=usgs.gov|publisher=[[International Astronomical Union]]|accessdate=4 March 2015}}</ref>
