'''''Burkholderia phage phiE12-2''''' is a [[bacteriophage]] (a [[virus]] that infects [[bacteria]]) of the family [[Myoviridae]], genus ''[[P2-like viruses]]''. Its genetic structure corresponds to the class I of the [[Baltimore classification]]: dsDNA, being a [[DNA virus]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://talk.ictvonline.org/files/ictv_documents/m/msl/4090.aspx|title= Master Species List of 2011, version 2|author= [[International Committee on Taxonomy of Viruses]] (ICTV) |year= 2011|accessdate=15 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|pmid=22481600|year=2012|last1=Adams|first1=MJ|last2=Carstens|first2=EB|title=Ratification vote on taxonomic proposals to the International Committee on Taxonomy of Viruses (2012)|volume=157|issue=7|pages=1411–22|doi=10.1007/s00705-012-1299-6|journal=Archives of Virology}}</ref>

