'''Explorer 28''' (or '''IMP-C''') was a satellite launched in May 1965 to study [[Space physics]]. It was powered by chemical batteries and [[Solar panels]]. There were 7 experiments onboard, all devoted to particle studies. Performance was normal until mid-April 1967, when intermittent problems began. It stayed in contact until May 12, 1967, when contact was lost. The orbit kept going lower and lower until it re-entered on July 4 1968.<ref>https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/nmc/spacecraftDisplay.do?id=1965-042A</ref>
