{{BLP sources|date=May 2010}} {{Infobox astronaut | image = USSR Stamp 1981 Salyut6 Cosmonauts.jpg | image_size = | caption = Leonid Popov and [[Valery Ryumin]] in USSR postage stamp, 1981 | name = Leonid Ivanovich Popov | type = Cosmonaut | nationality = [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] / [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1945|8|31}} | birth_place = [[Oleksandriia]], [[Ukrainian SSR]], [[USSR]] | occupation = [[aviator|Pilot]] | rank = [[Major General]], [[Soviet Air Force]] | selection = [[List_of_astronauts_by_selection#1970|Air Force Group 5]] | time = 200d 14h 45m | mission = [[Soyuz 35]]/[[Soyuz 37]], [[Soyuz 40]], [[Soyuz T-7]]/[[Soyuz T-5]] | insignia = | awards = [[Hero of the Soviet Union]] (2) }} '''Leonid Ivanovich Popov''' ({{lang-ru|Леони́д Ива́нович Попо́в}}; born August 31, 1945) is a former [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[cosmonaut]].
==Biography== Popov was born in [[Oleksandriia]], [[Kirovohrad Oblast]], [[Ukrainian SSR]]. He was selected as a cosmonaut on April 27, 1970, and flew as Commander on [[Soyuz 35]], [[Soyuz 40]] and [[Soyuz T-7]], logging 200 days, 14 hours, and 45 minutes in space before his retirement on June 13, 1987.<ref>http://www.spacefacts.de/bios/cosmonauts/english/popov_leonid.htm Spacefacts bio</ref> Popov is married with two children.
[[File:1983_CPA_5375_(1).jpg|thumb|none|Leonid Popov, [[Aleksandr Serebrov]] and [[Svetlana Savitskaya]]]] [[File:Prunariu with Brejnev.jpg|thumb|Leonid Popov and [[Dumitru Prunariu]] with [[Leonid Brezhnev]] in 1981]] He was awarded: *Twice [[Hero of the Soviet Union]]; *Three [[Order of Lenin|Orders of Lenin]]; *[[Medal "For Merit in Space Exploration"]] (Russian Federation); *[[Pilot-Cosmonaut of the USSR]]; *Honoured Master of Sport. Foreign awards: *Hero of the Socialist Republic of Romania; *[[Hero of the Republic of Cuba]] *Hero of Socialist Labour (Vietnam); *Order of Ho Chi Minh (Vietnam) .
