{{Infobox scientist |name = Lieuwe Dirk Boonstra |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = 1905 |birth_place = [[Volkrust]] ([[Transvaal Province]]) |death_date = 1975 |death_place = [[Cape town]] |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = |ethnicity = |field = Palaeontology |work_institutions = |alma_mater = |doctoral_advisor = |doctoral_students = |known_for = |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |prizes = |footnotes = }}
'''Lieuwe Dirk Boonstra''' (1905 – 1975) was a [[South Africa]]n [[paleontologist]] whose work focused on the [[therapsida|mammal-like reptiles]] of the Middle ([[Tapinocephalus Assemblage Zone|''Tapinocephalus'' Assemblage Zone]]) and Late [[Permian]], whose fossil remains are common in the South African [[Karroo]]. He was the author of a large number of papers on Therapsids and [[Pareiasaur]]s, and described and revised a number of [[species]].
==External links== * [https://web.archive.org/web/20060225165527/http://www.museums.org.za/sam/collect/infosci/boonstra.htm South African Museum - Dr. Boonstra's Publications]<!--dead link--> * [https://www.jstor.org/pss/3067935 Mention of the "late L.D. Boonstra"] * [https://books.google.com/books?id=g9kiAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Lieuwe+Dirk+Boonstra%22&dq=%22Lieuwe+Dirk+Boonstra%22&cd=1 Brief biography of Lieuwe Dirk Boonstra] * {{cite journal |author=Davis, Douglas |year=1979 |title=Dr. L. D. Boonstra se nagedagtenis gehuldig |journal= Matieland|volume= |issue= 3 |pages=41 |publisher= |doi= |pmid= |pmc= |url=http://hdl.handle.net/10019.1/4403 |accessdate=2012-04-12 |language=Afrikaans }}
