| active users            = 1,900
| total users             = 8,600
| active hosts            = 2,800
| total hosts             = 24,500
}}

'''MindModeling@Home''' is a non-profit research project that uses a combination of [[high performance computing]] and volunteer [[distributed computing]] for the advancement of [[cognitive science]]. The research focuses on utilizing computational [[cognitive model|cognitive process modeling]] to understand the human mind better. The project aims to improve on the scientific foundations that explain the mechanisms and processes that enable and moderate human performance and learning. MindModeling@Home is hosted by  [[Wright State University]] and the [[University of Dayton]] in Dayton, Ohio.

